# Expo Router Conventions

Routes live ONLY under `src/app/`. Entry is `expo-router/entry` (see `package.json` `main`).

## Structure

- Route groups in parens don't affect the URL: `(auth)`, `(tabs)`.
- Each segment with children has a `_layout.tsx` that renders a `<Stack>` or `<Tabs>`.
- Dynamic segments use brackets: `[certificateId]`, `[attachmentId]`.
- Modals: declare in the parent `<Stack.Screen>` with `presentation: 'modal'` (e.g. `upgrade-premium`).

```
app/
  _layout.tsx              # Root: SafeAreaProvider → AppProviders → StatusBar → AuthGate(Stack)
  (auth)/_layout.tsx       # welcome, login, register
  (tabs)/_layout.tsx       # <Tabs> with custom FloatingTabBar
    certificates/[certificateId]/...
```

## Rules

- Screens are thin: render UI + call feature hooks. NO Firebase/axios calls directly in route files.
- Get params with `useLocalSearchParams()`; navigate with `useRouter()` / `<Link>`. Use typed string routes like `/(tabs)/certificates`.
- Auth gating happens once in the root `AuthGate` (redirect via `router.replace` based on `useSegments()` + `useAuth()`). Don't re-implement auth redirects per screen.
- Configure headers/title via `screenOptions` / `<Stack.Screen options>`, sourcing styles from `Colors`.
- Private helper route files use an underscore prefix (`_FloatingTabBar.tsx`) so Router ignores them.
- Platform-specific route variants use platform suffixes (`scan.native2.tsx`, `scan.web2.tsx`).
